messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path:
  /printshops/{id}/pricetable/covers

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD acceptable: false
- POST acceptable: true
- OPTIONS acceptable: false
- TRACE acceptable: false
- GET acceptable: false
- PUT acceptable: true
- DELETE acceptable: false
- PATCH acceptable: false

Explanation:
- The addNewCoverItem handler is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{id}/pricetable/covers", method = RequestMethod.POST), so POST is explicitly allowed for the path /printshops/{id}/pricetable/covers.
- There is no class-level @RequestMapping, so the full path is exactly the value given on the method.
- The controller also defines editCoverItem with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{id}/pricetable/covers", method = RequestMethod.PUT), so PUT is explicitly allowed on the same path.
- No GET, DELETE, PATCH, HEAD, OPTIONS or TRACE mappings are declared in the source for this path; therefore, per the code (not framework runtime behavior), those methods are not acceptable.
